benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/resume - Resume a bundle

covered: Valid PUT Request Scenarios: The tests cover successful resume operations with 204 responses and state transitions for paused bundles (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04).
Non-Existing Resource: 404 when the bundle does not exist (TC05).
Input Validation & Error Handling: Invalid bundleId format (TC06), missing required header (TC07), invalid pluginProperty formats (TC19), past requestedDate (TC20).
State Management: Handling of non-paused (TC08) and cancelled (TC09) bundles to ensure proper error on invalid resume.
Query Parameters Coverage: Valid use of requestedDate and pluginProperty (TC02, TC03, TC04).
Partial Input: Resume with only required fields (TC18).
Edge Cases: Maximum header lengths (TC12) and maximum pluginProperty values (TC13).
Retry Mechanism & Resilience: Retry after transient network failure (TC15); integration degradation (TC25).
Audit/Logging: Reason/Comment captured in audit log when provided (TC04).
Performance/Load: Normal and peak load tests (TC22).
Regression/Edge Cases: Previously fixed edge cases (TC23).
Header Variations: Whitespace and case variations in X-Killbill-CreatedBy header (TC26).
Extra/Unexpected Parameters Handling: Extra query parameter foo=bar (TC11).
gaps: Rate Limiting: No tests cover rate limiting/throttling for repeated resume requests.
Caching Behavior: No tests for ETag/Cache-Control or client-side caching.
Pagination: Not applicable to a single PUT; no tests for bulk retrieval or pagination in this context.
Duplicate Submissions: No explicit handling of idempotency beyond concurrency scenario.
Date Format Variants: No tests for invalid date format in requestedDate (only past date covered).
Cross-Bundle Concurrency: Concurrency tests focus on a single bundle; no cross-bundle race conditions tested.
recommendations: Add rate-limiting/throttling tests for repeated PUT /resume calls to verify system resilience under load.
Add caching-related tests to verify proper caching headers or behavior if applicable.
Include tests for duplicate submissions and ensure idempotent semantics where relevant.
Add tests for invalid requestedDate formats (e.g., non-date string or wrong format).
Expand concurrency tests to cover cross-bundle scenarios and distributed environments.
Consider edge-case testing beyond 1000 pluginProperty values if future requirements change (scalability).
Include additional tests for legacy vs. new headers to ensure full backward compatibility at scale.
